---
import SectionHeading from "./SectionHeading.astro";
---

<section id="expertise" class="section">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-8">
    <div class="scroll-animate">
      <SectionHeading
        label="Focus"
        title="What I Do"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6 scroll-animate">
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground scroll-animate clip-reveal">
        I build <span class="font-pixel text-foreground">design systems</span> from the ground up — semantic tokens, component governance, release pipelines, and the documentation that makes adoption effortless. I've researched systems like Material Design 3, GitHub Primer, and Shopify Polaris to develop naming taxonomies and architecture patterns that scale across organizations.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground scroll-animate clip-reveal" style="animation-delay: 100ms">
        I author <span class="font-pixel text-foreground">product architecture</span> proposals — information architecture, competitive analysis, database schema design, and phased implementation plans. I think at the system level: how objects relate, how navigation should work, and how to reduce complexity for users and engineers alike.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground scroll-animate clip-reveal" style="animation-delay: 200ms">
        I champion <span class="font-pixel text-foreground">AI-forward engineering</span> — integrating tools like Claude Code into daily workflows, building AI agent features, and designing validation skills that catch issues before they ship. Good tooling compounds over time, and AI is the biggest force multiplier I've seen in my career.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
